{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]I'll just sit [C]back and watch you [G]leave
[D7]It seems you want more than I can give
[G]You don't care how [C]much my heart will [G]grieve
[D7]You've got to see how the other half [G]lives
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[C]Bright lights and smoke filled crowded [G]bars
[D7]Loud music that plays until all hours
[G]My today’s and [C]tomorrows I would [G]give
[D7]When you give up the way the other half [G]lives
{end_of_verse}

